caption: Have tried almost all of their meat tacos and Cochinita sandwich for delivery and everything was amazing. Would love to try this food closer to when it was made because it was really good.
The food is delicious and you can really taste the high quality of their ingredients. I thoroughly recommend this restaurant to everyone I know.

This restaurant is perfect for a get-together with friends or to unwind after a long day at the office. With its no-fuss interpretation of sophisticated comfort food, their good food menus entice guests from all over the world.
This place never disappoints! They have the kindest staff too!

I loved everything about this place. The staff were genuinely friendly, it was clean, and received a good amount of (amazing) food. There are lots of options including vegan options that see-saw between Korean and Mexican which I loved. I ordered three tacos- the Vegan Forastero, the Bulgogi one, and the Cameron one. Each one was exciting bite by bite and loaded with filling--They also did not skimp on filling these tacos thankfully which I worry about when spending $4 on a taco. The cameron taco was my favorite due to the sauce on it. It was sweet, savory, a little sour, a little spicy, and super creamy. Contrasted with the crunchy breaded shrimp was incredible. I hardly write reviews but felt compelled to after eating here.
Honestly the best food in chicago. This place never disappoints! They have the kindest staff too!
This place is incredible. Had the Korean BBQ and Kalbi tacos with some Dak wings. Blew mind away. A must try, will come back for sure.

ordered on the website / through ChowNow - highly recommend that over other delivery apps because the restaurant gets all of the order profit! Tried the Korean BBQ pork tacos, Sesame Kalbi tacos, and kimchi fries. LOVED the Korean BBQ tacos Didn’t love the fries but that’s just personal preference - overall I would recommend this place!
I had the jerk macaroni bowl for the first time and I fell in love !!! This is a perfect combination and you can taste every season. Definitely will be coming back.
Best！
Best tacos. Vegan shrimp tacos too

My fiancé and I fell in love with the smoked flavor of the black beans and rice, and the vegan shrimp tacos are addictive.  The shrimp have a really good texture that I had to double check a few times to ensure they were vegan. The person who took our order over the phone was very pleasant and helpful.  We will be back over and over.
Huge portions, super fresh, and delicious!

FLAVOR TOWN! Love the fusion. Tamales with Asian slaw <3. Shrimp taco is omg delicious, that sauce! Bebimbop is absolutely delicious. I love the family that runs this place! Thank you so much for fantastic food, I hope you hang tight during this awful shut down!

Strongly recommended restaurant in the region! I always brought my family to this affordable and incredible restaurant. I was so happy with the service because they treated their customers in a very nice way. The foods are so cool and delicious. I love the ambiance of the place because it was so classy. Five stars for you, guys! Cheers!

The Mexican and Asian fusion was a treat! We had The Ship, Dak Wings and Kung Fu Wings, Fish Taco and Horchata! Everything was Great! The Owner was a gem and the staff were very friendly. We will be back.
Excellent vegan options.  You gotta try the vegan shrimp tacos  and the vegan terriaki tacos.
A tasty place for unique Mexican-Asian fusion 'tacos' and bowls !

I was so excited to try this place out knowing how many vegan options they had but it pains me to say that I was very disappointed. We ordered the three vegan tacos, kimchi fries, rice and beans and the horchata. The kimchi fries were good and the rice and beans were flavorful with the slight smoky taste but the tacos were under seasoned. We had to add loads on salt to make them palatable. I hope they improve on the taste and I will definitely try the place again. I definitely want to encourage restaurants that have vegan items on the menu. Another minor note but the individual taking our order wasn't particularly helpful or welcoming. Again, might just be having a bad day but affected the experience a little bit. I did like the menu and wouldn't mind going back for the rice and beans
We love the atmosphere here. Very welcoming and the staff are very nice and welcoming. Ah, the food is amazing!
The owners/ workers are so friendly and nice! The food is amazing, definitely recommend the Dak wings and the Korean BBQ tacos. Delish!!
Great tacos. Lots of flavor and big portions!
Absolutely wonderful. The service was great but the food....delicious. Everything is fresh and made to order and is served hot. If you haven't been here, you should.  Highly recommend.
Great place for korean fusion. Food is delicious, lots of cool options like kimchi fries which we like. Friendly staff.
Delicious, so fresh, clean & the happy feeling you get when you leave this place is amazing.
My favorite place in the city. I eat here at least once per week and the quality is top notch. I suggest getting any of the tacos (especially the shrimp and fish one) and the bibimbop.
I enjoyed their tinga de pollo taco, sesame Kalbi taco and hibiscus water. Definitely recommend this place for mexican and korean food!
The best fish tacos and horchata I’ve ever had!!

The food here is spectacular! The wings and tacos have such a unique and flavorful taste, you'll love it. The staff is also very friendly and helpful. Highly recommended if you're a fan of Korean and Mexican food or just looking to try something unique!

I don’t write reviews for things, but this is one of the best restaurants in Chicago. The food is absurdly good and fun and the owners are exceptionally kind. The first time I came in, they stopped by my table asking how the food was. The second time I came in, they gave me coupons for stopping by again. The third time I came in, they knew my name and my order.  The food is ridiculously good and the couple that owns the restaurant are the nicest people possible.  If you’re in Old Town (or Chicago), eat here!

The tacos were excellent, 5/5. The bibimbop sandwich wasn't as great, 3/5. Overall, a solid experience and we will likely return for more unique tacos or to try out some of their other creative menu options.

I got the chicken sandwich, but was surprised by what I got. There were a lot of great veggies on it and I liked the substance, but I think I would've liked it a little wetter. The hoagie was toasted a bit much, so if you like it nice and crunchy, I recommend this!  I also got the kimchi fries. These were fries covered in kimchi, Sriracha, and cheese. The cheese was mid quality but all in all, I liked the taste. Excited to try the tacos next time I visit!
Simply the best! I live nearby and probably have been 30 times, the shrimp tacos are da bomb! Show them some love
Pan Asian and Mexican dishes are tasty and fresh. Lots of veggie options too

Came here with some homies after a bike caravan. Great vegan options! First time there I only had the kimchi fries wich were spicy & delicious. Second time there i had the flautas, forastero taco, & soy chorizo taco. The flautas were exquisite. The forastero taco was interesting and fresh, something different from your typical taco but good. Last but not least the chorizo taco was flame and they give a hefty amount of food in each taco. The customer service is phenomal. Really nice mexican lady she even offered my friends and I the chance to refill our water bottles with cold water. Btw theyre byob! Overall 12/10.
Some of the best tacos in the city!
Picked up tacos for dinner, we definitely be back to try more!

Def not same place as Sunnyvale. .. don't get confused thinking the same experience you had there will be same as here.  Staff is no as involved with you, not very happy, priced more, and music choice isn't fitting.  And somehow the chicken is "smaller".

I ordered the Bibimbap chicken rice bowl and their cinco de mayo taco special which included an amazing jasmine rice and beans combo with two tacos ! I got the classic Forastero Taco and The Big Bird and they were absolutely perfect.  Normally I would get the Tamales which are also phenomenal but got Kimchi Fries and they were equally as satisfying!  This was the perfect Cinco de Mayo Dinner combined with the CBD iced tea ! I highly recommend ordering pick up, if you can, because less fees on both ends.
Great Korean Mexican fusion tacos. My favorite was fish taco and bulgogi taco. Flavorful and their tortilla was good too!
Food was delicious!! Really amazing menu, tough choices but everything we ordered really surpassed our expectations. Tacos, kimchi fries and dak wings were all amazing 😍👏
What a great place.  Total package of great service, drinks and food.  Burger is truly outstanding.  Great atmosphere.  I will be back

In chicago on vacation and i found that the majority of restaurants here are bland BUT NOT THIS ONE. The food is so flavorful and its so affordable. I’m sad that I won’t be able to have it again. 😭 seriously THE BEST!
Excellent crossover: Korean meets Mexican! Wonderful tacos like Korean BBQ or spicy shrimp. Very V E R Y casual. Also - BYOB. Note: great fries!
Amazing! Kimchi fried to die for! Will return soon.
Good food
Amazing food, amazing service. Place is clean and cozy.
Soooooo good!!! the esta camaron tacos are delicious. Two tacos for less than $10 was filling at a great price. Highly recommend
Way better than expected, small and bustling. Try the kimchi fries!
Great food with different flavors and the best tacos
Such a good hybrid between Korean and tacos!
(Translated by Google) All very rich, and very friendly 💕  (Original) Todo muy rico, y muy amables 💕

I don't leave a ton of Google reviews, but I couldn't let myself go to bed tonight without reviewing this place. It's amazing. The food is top notch and delicious, but what really shines is the staff. They really go above and beyond to help you with whatever you need. I'd never felt so welcome in a restaurant, and the love and vision that goes into this small business is truly inspiring. It made me proud to call Chicago my home. Thank you for a great meal!
Phenomenal food, service was great and prices too
The service is great, and the food is awesome! A great combination of the two classic, mexican + korean

Surprisingly delicious combination of flavors and ingredients. They have ramen, kimchi fries, tacos. Very reasonably priced, do not expect a white tablecloths restaurant (pay at the moment of placing your order), it is family owned and operated. Definitely scrumptious. BYOB.

Korean Mexican mashup restaurant. What is surprising is the vegetarian and Vegan options. They have a couple of tacos, bibimbap, kimchi fries, Rice and beans... I was surprised by how much flavor there was in the Rice and beans. The tacos were well seasoned and filling. I haven't had the Bibimbap yet. Next time.  I am assuming their meat stuff is good too. 😃.
Top notch flavors. Service the best. Ambiance very attractive. Recommended!
Best tacos!

Very nice concept since i love Korean and Mexican food, portions are good, the owners are nice and attentive, good service but a little short on flavor and i say this because i know both cuisines; I'll come back if I'm in the area
This place is great! The tacos were exceptional and portions were generous.
Food is great. Service not so much. I waited 45 minutes to get my order and when I got it it was wrong!!!! They are poorly organized. A real shame because the food is good.
Awesome tacos!
The shrimp tacos are the best I've ever had. The Mexican/Korean fusion is one I would of never thought of.
Best fusion food spot!!!
Huge portions and friendly staff!
Veggie options are ok

So so good! The family behind the counter are the sweetest and you feel the love and thought that goes into every delicious dish. We rode bikes there and brought a bottle of wine (they’re BYOB) and ordered way too much. The wings were GREAT!  As were all the different tacos we got!
Superb food & service. You have to try this place!

Came here on a late Friday night with a large party. I was eyeing this place all day and chose to end our night here because of the great reviews. This place did not disappoint at all with quality in food, service and value. My friends and I ordered everything from the kalbi bibimbap, kim chi fries, Korean wings, Korean bbq sandwhich, horchata, ga fish, porky pig, sesame kalbi and the kiss tacos. The tacos I mentioned are a must order. Meats are well seasoned, cooked perfectly and theres plenty of meat. Its asian fusion at its best. The wings were average in size, but the sauce was a lil too tart and thick. Piping hot and still very good. The bibimbap and kim chi fries are a must order as well. The combination of flavors and the hot bowl were perfect. It was so good that between the 8 of us we were fight between the last grain of rice. The fries are packed with plenty of meat and kim chi. If you love this combination of flavors definitely order this dish.  Overall, this is a great place to come for lunch or dinner. We saw people placing a bunch of carry out orders. The location itself is staffed very well and kept very clean. Food came out really quick and we loved our experience. I'll definitely be back here next time I'm in town to try more of their dishes.
Nice cozy place with great vegan options. Good service.

Great fusion taco joint,  very clean and welcoming. Open till 2am with free late night street parking.  The good is very well balanced,  so it's hard to share just one taco (order 2)  dont mess with their ratios they are really good the way they are.

I can’t remember the last time I went somewhere and couldn’t figure out which option was my favorite. Everything was delicious. Esta cameron - crunchy and sweet. Kalbi taco - smoky and delicious. bulgogi sandwich was like a crispy Korean bahn mi. The kimchi fries were so unique - who knew cheese and kimchi worked together. And finally, the bi bim bop was perfectly portioned (nothing overwhelmed) and the rice was crispy deliciousness on the bottom.
Good food, reasonably priced, and quick

(Translated by Google) Vegetarian and vegan options very rich. It is a simple place but with rich, varied food at a good price. I have tried their two vegan tacos and I have loved them! They make Korean-Mexican fusion.  (Original) Opciones vegetarianas y veganas muy ricas. Es un lugar sencillo pero con comida rica, variada y a buen precio. Yo he probado sus dos tacos veganos y me han encantado! Hacen fusión koreano-mexicano.

Amazing food if you are looking for Korean and Mexican fusion. Plenty of Vegan options on the menu makes it even more appealing. The serving portions for the Tacos are a little small for the price but the quality and the taste are very good. Would definitely recommend this place to my friends.
Food was delicious!! My party of 12 loved all the food, from Vegan to Gluten Free, to my non-picky eaters. 🔥 place!
Restaurant is excellent. Food is fantastic. Support your local restaurants!
Amazing food
Fairly disappointed 😔
The food in this place is AMAZING!!! It was such a pleasant surprise to experience this Korean-Mexican fusion cuisine that we've never had before! We will DEFINITELY be back again!!😄
These are some of the best tacos I've ever had. The Korean bbq, and fish tacos are a flavour explosion! These are generously portioned and assembled with care.
Byob and delicious.  Good for groups and very informal.
Pretty good comfort food place. I will suggest their esta camaron (shrimp tacos)... I didn't like their fish tacos though
Love their bulgogi sandwich and bimbinbop 👌🏾
The Fish or shrimp Tacos are the Best i've had !!
Delicious Mexican Korean fusion joint with tasty tacos and sandwiches

Great little side restaurant with a flair for flavor.  As a table we had 5 different kinds of tacos and every one had a unique flavor.   It was incredible!   We had pork,  chicken,  big bird, beef, vegan and my favorite - shrimp.  But the flavors were so different is what is so amazing.   Oh,  we also had the Kim chi fries which are like nacho/stacked/ loaded potatoes.   Very yummy.   A little spicy but not too spicy.   Gluten free options.   Vegetarian options

Delicious - Crazy Korean/Mexican fusion. The Kahbil taco was an explosion of flavor. The tamales were so light and fluffy and filled with slow roasted pork with pickled veg. Had the Kimchi fries but we are them so fast I didn't have time to take a picture...cheese pork goodness with a wonderful spicy Kimchi.
Food was delicious!
The Esta Camaron taco was so good that we had to order a second round of them.
Fish taco is amazing. Everything else is mediocre.
Friendly and thoughfully prepared.
Exceptional!
Okay
Amazing fish tacos and the bibimbap is a must have
Killer fusion tacos with quick and friendly service. Reasonable prices and great flavor is always a winning combination.
That place was absolutely awesome!!

That fish taco is HUGE!! I came here with a group and we got the shrimp taco, lengua taco, dak wings, kimchi fries 👌👌👌, and tamales. All in all a fantastic experience as everything tasted phenomenal. They really know how to utilize citrus in their sauces and marinades. Their shrimp taco my favorite so far!
Delicious bibimbap and vegan options. The ginger cbd tea is very drinkable.
Great selection on the menu! And the food was perfect. Will definitely be going back.

Best fish tacos I've ever had. I dined in here a couple of months ago on a double date, and I just had take-out last night. I absolutely love it. Everything about the food at Forastero is done perfectly: the flavors, the textures, the freshness of the ingredients, did I mention the flavors? The tamales were some of the best I've ever had (two for $6 is a steal!) The pork in the tamales was tender, perfectly fatty, generously portioned, and seasoned to perfection. The wings and the kimchi fries are the bomb. All of the tacos are awesome- great flavor and ingredient combinations (but the Crispy Fish taco is hands down the best). There's plenty of seating, they have daily specials, and they're BYOB! Service is quick and friendly, and you can tell the owner really cares about his patrons and his business. I will continue coming here and will rave to everyone I know about this hidden gem in Chicago.
Fantastic!!! Never been to a fusion and this was amazing. I had the soup with the ramen noodles and it was so good! Definitely coming back to try more! BYOB was a plus too!
Excellent food. Can't wait to come back for more!

I had Korean BBQ, Shrimp, and Pork tacos ....I gotta tell you that they were exceptional. I love Mexican and eat it sometimes 3 days a week, the tacos at Forasteros were not only well prepared but they were also delicious. Moist, juicy and seasoned perfectly.
Had the bulgogi sandwich and kimchi fries. Just stellar! Byob as well. Try it out, you won't be disappointed.

Never had this type of food before and so I decided to step outside my comfort zone. Fish tacos were AMAZING!!! The Big Bird taco, Korean chicken and a spicy sauce was tasty as well! The atmosphere is pleasant and laid back and I’m happy that I ventured away from my norm.
What a great place. Amazing tacos and lovely service.
100% the best place in Old Town. Esta Camaron tacos are shrimps tacos, and you can’t miss them! Kimchi fries were great too.
Best tacos I’ve ever had in Chicago!!! Loved the go fish, porky pig, and cannot forget about the kimchi fries! Highly recommend for dinner and late night noms.
Had an amazing experience, fish and shrimp tacos were AMAZING, as well as kimchi fries. Would come back every day if I could!

First time at this restaurant, I heard lots of good things from here and seen lost of post of social media about this place. All I can really say is... I LOVE IT! The mixture of Mexican and Korean is so good! I also order some wings and they are super good and good price. Also good price per a taco cause they really fill up the taco. I did order the horchata but it wasn't the best, it was a little to thick to my liking but good flavor. I will be coming back to this place.
Delicious veggie bibimbop!

Do not order the ramen soup. It’s way too salty, better off drinking ocean water. The fusion Tacos were okay, not impressed. I wouldn’t recommend this place as it was my 1st and last time. It’s either too sweet or too salty. The service was pleasant.
Plates came out staggered so there was always one to two items on the table at a time. They were also accommodating to our party of four by adding a fourth item to a 3 item plate. Great time!
This place is amazing!! I ordered 3 different tacos and they were all absolutely delicious.  Can’t wait to go back- especially since they’re byob! Definitely a neighborhood go to
This is a very interesting flavored resturaunt that makes your mouth water with all of its intricate exotic flavors
This place is absolutely exceptional. I’ve eaten there 5+ times, and constantly talk people into going. Each time, my friends have become regulars.

Very casual Korean/Mexican fusion place: order at the counter, take a number, food gets dropped on your table, though not at the same time. We had four in our party. One friend received his food right away, and the other orders arrived slowly and haphazardly; by the time his partner got her food, he was long finished. I ordered the Vegan Al Pastor and Vegan Forastero Tacos, but they were evidently out of ingredients for the latter item and replaced it with a second Al Pastor taco. They were both OK, lightly seasoned and rather dry. Everyone was content with their food, but it's certainly not a place I'd seek out: at 6:00 PM on a Saturday night they were out of one of their 4 vegetarian items. There was no ice in the soda machine. The table needed a wipe-down. And so on.
Authentic korean-mexican cuisine
Simply amazing. Every bite of food has a Hurst of flavor. Definitely will be back!

The food is wonderful and not too pricey. The staff are amazingly helpful and courteous. I received great assistance from the management when I helped organize a party that turned out to be a great success

We were craving Korean flavors and decided to dine in.  Great flavors, nice staff, overall a wonderful experience.  The bibimbap was very tasty, the tacos were outstanding.  And it's BYOB!  We will definitely be back!

I love this place. The food is spectacular. Sandwiches and wings are delicious. They also have deals M-F that are a great value. Everytime we dine in, Jessie goes above and beyond and takes service to another level. She is so considerate!
We love having this unique option in the neighborhood.
Fantastic flavors and byob
Awesome grub!
Amazing tacos!  Never tasted anything like them.  Can't wait to try the rest of the menu!  I've walked by here too many times - what a gem to have in the neighborhood.

Go Fish is a unique taco experience. I enjoy it every time. Flavors are nicely mixed and the size is simply decadent. While the general pricing for quality does not match many of the Mexican places, if you want a Korean taco, this is the place. And oh yeah, they have vegan options, bibimbamp, and bhan mi as well.

If you want a great taste then "Forastero Restaurant" is a perfect place to enjoy.A wonderful blend of flavors and authenticity make this a favorite.Delicious and unique food and great price.Their friendly atmosphere and nice music is truly alluring.The staff is conversational and very friendly.The interior is very clean & service is great.Finally "Forastero Restaurant" is a true gem in the neighborhood!!  From GKNInT SECRET SHOPPER.
Super cool restaurant with vegan options. Staff is really friendly and helpful!
Amazing tacos—very friendly staff.
(Translated by Google) Excellent cervicio and very tasty the sanduichs of cochinita pibill  (Original) Exelente cervicio y muy sabroso el sanduichs de cochinita pibill
Dope food and amazing menu. RC cola fountain was a nice touch

Korean Mexican fusion is an interesting concept and they have a pretty interesting and tasty-looking menu. I got the Korean BBQ sandwich and kimchi fries. Both were tasty, but admittedly I got the more Korean dishes so I didn't feel the fusion. They have good vegan options, my vegan friend enjoyed her meal (vegan kimchi fries and vegan floutas). Overall nice decor, BYOB, chill atmosphere, medium amount of seating. I would consider coming back here to try to rest of the menu.

What an amazing place in an unassuming stretch of North Avenue. An unlikely fusion of Korean and Mexican food results in spicy, tangy and wonderful pallet of flavors. Each dish seems to top the high praise I offered the previous meal and I am excited to return. Run by a father and son team giving it their all, you absolutely need to eat here! Plus they seem to have a green thumb with a bunch of indoor plants creating an oxygen rich environment inside.
Excellent Tacos with a Korean flair
Good shrimp tacos. Comparable to Del Seoul.
My favorite lunch spot! The food is really good, and staff is nice. They do make your food really quickly too!
Delicious food and amazing service. I will definitely be back.
Delicious food. Amazing service. And reasonable services.
Go Fish and Korean BBQ tacos. Yum!

A neat Korean / Latin fusion take out joint with some seating inside a small dining room.   Tacos were good.  Dishes with shrimp were better than those with chicken in our opinion, but all were good.  Menu is not huge,  but includes sandwiches,  tacos,  rice bowls and bibimbop.

Stopped in today with a friend for a late lunch and was so impressed! This place keeps coming up as one of the top rated places in the area and for good reason! We tried a shrimp taco, a fish taco, and a Korean bbq pork sandwich. All absolutely fantastic. Two very minor complaints: the piece of fish was a little too big to actually eat it as a taco but we didn’t really care because it was so delicious. Also, bread on the sandwich was just slightly too toasted which made for a few very crunchy bites but these things were so minor that the flavors and quality of the food far outweighed them. You’ve got to check this place out!
Our go to place. Great wings and tacos and sandwiches
(Translated by Google) I love the place my favorite dish the bowl  (Original) Me encanta el lugar mi plato preferido el bowl
Awesome food - made teleport to Mexico and South East Asia! Great ambiance :) people there are super nice!!!
Very tasty tacos. Had 5 different kinds. Good service. Reasonable prices.
Fantastic food - the tacos were excellent! Would recommend the Big Fish and BBQ Pork in particular.
I love their take on Korean-Mexican fusion. The Korean beef taco is fantastic
Great food, plus great vegan options if you are into that sort of thing.  Definitely a hidden gem.  Have been back several times.
Great food, the staff is conversational and very friendly. Friendly atmosphere and nice music.
Great restaurant with great vegetarian and vegan options! We loved the bibimbap and the tofu tacos. Would definitely recommend.
Really good food
Cheap and high-quality tacos.  Highly recommended!

This was the first time trying the Bibimop and it was amazing. All the different flavors just melt in your mouth. The sauce that it comes with is the perfect mixture of sweet and sour. The bowl is very hot and keeps the food hot the entire time. It also helped cook the egg once it was mixed in. I’ve had a few different tacos from here (all of them delish!) but these are the Porky Pig, Sesame Kalbi and Korean BBQ Pork. The meat serving is extremely generous. Each taco combination was very different. All of the flavors mix so well in every bite. I’m already planning to go there for more Bibimop soon!
The bulgogi sandwich was delicious!
Delicious food. Amazing service. Quick! Reasonable. Tasty! BYOB! Need I say more? Yum!
Great Korean Mexican fusion, true, but honestly the best part of the meal was the fries. Highly recommend
Tacos are too expensive at $4 each, but overall the quality is fabulous and the owners are from Mexico City. Very authentic !

Came here after Thai Aroma closed down and were finding another spot nearby. Very good. A cool fusion of Korean and Mexican food. Counter service which is nice for bigger groups. BYOB. I’ve been back multiple times.

Good value and great flavors. Extremely friendly staff that came around to ask about the meal. The tacos tasted fresh and flavorful and the bulgogi bowl was hot enough to crisp the rice like a stone bowl. We were even offered Korean sweets at the end of the meal.
First time dining here but i'll be back. Good food, good service, good owners. Thanks, Andy
You seriously cannot go wrong with anything on this menu.
Fantastic shrimp tacos, great fish tacos, and awesome kimchii fries. Highly recommend, very friendly, family owned place
The portions were good the services was great very polite!

This hidden gem is a small family owned place with an amazing twist on Mexican tacos.  The owner was very friendly.  Every taco I ordered was solid and it was fairly cheap.  I will be back here everytime I'm in the area
Great food, servers can be conversational and very casual. Friendly atmosphere and nice music.
Finally tried this place for the first time - highly recommend! Their tacos and bibimbop were fantastic, the Go Fish taco was great! Will definitely be back again.
The Ship sandwich and the fries were delicious! The interior was very clean and looked great. Owner and staff were very friendly. We'll be back!
BYOB. Delicious Korean-Mexican fusion. Great prices. Hidden gem.
Friendly owner and staff. Food was delicious and a perfectly balanced fusion. BYOB and the price is right!
I prefer their tacos over Del Seoul's, and the location is less crazy.  Unfortunately, they use styrofoam for their to go containers.
Amazing tacos, good Bilbumbop, but the kimchi fries are just perfect: Good appetizer but better as a post drinking food.
Great food, the kim chi fries are delicious! The folks who work there are very friendly and helpful... definitely worth a visit!
Good tasting food!
Bulgolgi bibimop is excellent. The zucchini and shiitake mushrooms are too die for !

awesome spot. just down the street from my office. had the chicken sandwich and was blown away. so delicious, will definitely have to try other options. Mad at myself that I didn't try this spot earlier.

Randomly found this place and the food was excellent. DAK WINGS are exceptionally good. THE SHIP sandwich was fantastic. Highly recommend this place. Tony "the owner" is so welcoming and friendly!  Thank you,  Satisfied customer!

So good! Amazing tacos. I especially like the shrimp ones (Cameron I think). Great service and consistently delicious food. I think the location isn’t ideal because this place should be way more crowded! If you’re  walking down north ave. it’s defiantly worth stopping in!

Wow. The reviews on this place were right on!! Food is amazing. Korean/Mexican fusion. Really creative and delicious. The place is small and very casual. You order at the register and then grab a seat. They've only been open 10 months. Find it and support them so they stay in business.
Delicious and unique fusion fare. Lovingly prepared by the family members. Always a winner.
Good food

The food here is spectacular! The wings and tacos have such a unique and flavorful taste, you'll love it. The staff is also very friendly and helpful. Highly recommended if you're a fan of Korean and Mexican food or just looking to try something unique!
Wonderful Korean Latin fusion!  The tacos are all super flavorful.  I especially love the fish taco and the tingo chicken.  We tried the bimbob too and loved it as well.
My new FAVORITE restaurant in Chicago! We ordered some tacos, a bowl and some fries and were so impressed and satisfied with everything. I was too hungry to take pictures but I wish I had! Delicious!
Great place.
Great Mexican Korean fusion, and BYOB. I came in a group of 4 and we had kimchi fries and 6 tacos. The tacos had great unique flavors and were a good size.. I will be back.
The food here is amazing and the people that work here are some of the nicest people I've met. Definitely check this place out!

The menu, the price, and the people make this a no-brainer. Tacos are phenomenal and the portion sizes put other spots to shame. A wonderful blend of flavors and authenticity make this a favorite.

These flavors at these prices are a godsend in this neighborhood. I've been here several times in the month or so they've been open, and it's been consistently delicious. My reigning favorite taco is the fish- a very generous helping of nicely fried fish with a real kick  to the sauce. In terms of Korean tacos city -wide, I would say this place is not *quite* as good as Del Seoul or Tacorea (RIP), but it sure beats the hell out of just about everywhere else nearby in terms of flavor-to-dollar value. Next time you're grabbing a bite before heading to the comedy show or the club, skip the $14 burger on Wells and walk the two blocks over here.
